2026-04-16 12:15:36 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 6'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show correct 12 V and return up to the input of Control Module 6, with all cables thereafter floating at near 0 V on both conductors. There is no polarity inversion detected anywhere. This means the series path from the PSU to downstream modules is opened inside Control Module 6 (or its outgoing terminals), not in the wiring between modules. The most likely root cause is an internal open circuit in the 12 V line (e.g., failed or miswired switch, broken trace, or bad connector) within Control Module 6, preventing supply from reaching modules 7–8 and the load module. Replacing/repairing Control Module 6 should restore power and allow the downstream indicators and lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
